1 AN ACT relating to a supplemental payment for retired state employees, making an
2 appropriation therefor, and declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS 61.691 to the contrary and
5 subject to the limitations established by this section, recipients of a monthly retirement
6 allowance from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System or State Police Retirement
7 System shall receive a one-time supplemental payment added to their July 2025
8 retirement allowance payment, equal to the monthly retirement allowance the recipient
9 receives from the system in the month of June 2025.
10 Section 2. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of
11 $95,000,000 in fiscal year 2024-2025 from the Budget Reserve Trust Fund Account
12 established by KRS 48.705 to the Kentucky Public Pensions Authority to be applied to
13 the following funds to prefund the supplemental payment provided by Section 1 of this
14 Act:
15 (1) $84,000,000 to the Kentucky Employees Retirement Fund of the Kentucky
16 Employees Retirement System established by KRS 61.515 to prefund the supplemental
17 payment from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System to each recipient for service
18 in a nonhazardous position as defined in KRS 61.510(44);
19 (2) $6,000,000 to the Kentucky Employees Retirement Fund of the Kentucky
20 Employees Retirement System established by KRS 61.515 to prefund the supplemental
21 payment from the Kentucky Employees Retirement System to each recipient for service
22 in a hazardous position as provided in KRS 61.592; and
23 (3) $5,000,000 to the State Police Retirement Fund of the State Police Retirement
24 System established by KRS 16.510 to prefund the supplemental payment from the State
25 Police Retirement System to each recipient.
26 Section 3. Whereas retired members and beneficiaries of the Kentucky
27 Employees Retirement System and State Police Retirement System have not received a
